{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nBug 5e40 (auto-lander epic f1fa), verified from the store: a blocking E2/F1 finding with a FALSE absence premise ('the plan never tasks anyone with capturing the pre-cutover snapshot') survived Pass-2 at validity 0.94, picked up hard-override axes (impact 0.85), and blocked — while a G3 advisory in the SAME verdict quoted the very provision the block claimed absent (norm ne7642adbf79, 07-12 11:44 verdict; the plan text contains actor, artifact path infra/gerrit/access-snapshot-pre-autolander.json, and timing). Separately: DET findings fire contentless ('Sibling tickets touch the same file(s) with no ordering edge' — naming no tickets/files, unadjudicable), and plan-review criteria are blind to ADR-0043's [operator-attested] tag, demanding in-session proving commands for ACs the completion gate accepts by recorded attestation. Design approved by operator 2026-07-12; each component preserves the four-pass separation (pass 1 discovers, pass 2 answers narrow binaries, pass 3 drops deterministically, pass 4 coaches non-prescriptively).\n\n## What\nCOMPONENT 1 — absence-claim grounding veto:\n- Pass 1: UNCHANGED (independence invariant, ADR 0008).\n- Pass 2: add two abstain-safe binaries to the shared verification contract (src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/verify.py + the verifier prompts): `claims_absence` ('does this finding's premise assert something is missing/never specified/not tasked? yes/no' — classifies the FINDING text) and `absence_confirmed_in_context` ('search the plan text provided; is there any provision matching the item claimed absent? quote it if found; yes/no/insufficient' — a lookup against the context the verifier already re-grounds on). Missing answers abstain (no effect), like the plan-v2 axes.\n- Pass 3: deterministic veto in src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/decide.py, symmetric to the existing cited-reference veto (decide.py:318-326): claims_absence == yes AND absence_confirmed_in_context == no -> dropped (premise-refuted). No threshold changes.\n- Pass 4: unchanged.\nCOMPONENT 2 — DET finding content floor:\n- Audit the DET emitters and fix ONLY those that actually fire contentless findings. NOTE: the P5 interference detector (det_floor.py:491-509) ALREADY emits subjects — it is NOT a target. The fix targets the emitters that genuinely omit subjects despite computing them (the P6-class sibling-overlap detector and any peer the audit flags); record the audit result (which emitters were non-compliant) in the change. Detectors already compute the subjects (ticket ids, file paths, AC line refs), so this is surfacing them in evidence/location, not recomputing.\n- Backstop: a deterministic hygiene rule SCOPED TO DET-TIER findings only — a DET finding with no location and no concrete evidence spans is unadjudicable and drops. IMPLEMENTATION HOOK: DET findings never enter `pass3_over_findings` (they flow through `det_blocking_findings`/`det_advisory_findings` in `plan_review/det_floor.py:932/942` → `partition_findings` in `orchestrator.py:380`), so the backstop must be applied AT that DET emission/aggregation point (in `det_blocking_findings`/`det_advisory_findings`, or at the `partition_findings` boundary), NOT inside `pass3_over_findings`. It never touches LLM-tier findings (they never pass through the DET emitters).\nCOMPONENT 3 — operator-attested AC awareness:\n- Detection is pure DET (exact case-insensitive prefix per ADR 0043). INJECTION POINT: it is injected into each finding's `severity_attributes` as a boolean field `operator_attested` inside `plan_review/workflow_ops.py` `plan_review_decide` (workflow_ops.py:324 — the step that reshapes per-finding verifications into the `{index: {severity_attributes, binary}}` map Pass-3 consumes), mirroring how `code_review/workflow_ops.py:278-301` DET-enriches churn90/hard_to_reverse_surface. Pass 2 receives it as a fact, never judges it.\n- Pass 1: the E2/F1/E6 rubric prompts gain the ADR-0043 vocabulary — a tagged AC is verifiable by recorded attestation; absence of in-session proving commands is not, by itself, a finding against it.\n- Pass 3: deterministic suppression keyed on the DET flag. MECHANISM: `impact_plan` (decide.py) reads `attrs.get('ac_unverifiable')` and applies a 0.85 floor when it is non-none. Suppression is implemented by REMOVING (or setting to `None`) the `ac_unverifiable` key from that finding's `severity_attributes` when `operator_attested` is set — done in `plan_review_decide` while assembling the Pass-3 attrs map, BEFORE `impact_plan` reads it (not a branch inside `impact_plan`, which stays byte-unchanged). \"Sole basis\" = only the `ac_unverifiable` axis is cleared; every other axis (validity, other severity attrs) is untouched, so a finding that also fires another axis still survives with its non-ac_unverifiable impact. This keeps the kernel `impact_plan`/`pass3` math unchanged (the fact is injected upstream; the kernel is not taught about operator-attestation).\n- Pass 4: one new coaching move — 'state the concrete attestation evidence the tagged AC will require'.\nEXCLUDED (explicit non-goal): comment-trail consultation in any form — a self-refutation channel the completion verifier deliberately defends against; revisit only if post-fix field data shows surviving re-litigation friction.\n\n## Scope\nsrc/rebar/llm/review_kernel/verify.py + decide.py (contract binaries + the absence-claim deterministic veto — `impact_plan`/`pass3` math stays byte-unchanged), `plan_review/workflow_ops.py` (`plan_review_decide` — inject the `operator_attested` DET flag into severity_attributes and clear `ac_unverifiable` upstream of `impact_plan`), the plan-review verifier prompts (both single-turn and agentic variants), plan_review/det_floor.py + the sibling-overlap detector (subject emission + the DET-tier hygiene backstop at the DET emission/aggregation point), E2/F1/E6 rubric prompts, the coach MOVE_REGISTRY, tests. The f1fa 11:44 verdict (norm ne7642adbf79 + G3 n0eb3f2e9da9) becomes a regression fixture.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The verification contract carries claims_absence and absence_confirmed_in_context with abstain-safe defaults; older/absent verifiers change nothing (byte-compat test on the base model).\n- [ ] Pass 3 drops a finding when claims_absence=yes and absence_confirmed_in_context=no; a regression fixture replaying the f1fa 11:44 false-absence finding is dropped, while a TRUE absence claim survives.\n- [ ] DET P5/P6-class findings name their subjects (tickets/files/AC lines); the DET-scoped hygiene backstop drops a subject-less DET finding and a test proves it never touches LLM-tier findings.\n- [ ] The [operator-attested] tag is DET-detected and injected into severity_attributes; a tagged AC's in-session-unverifiability finding loses the ac_unverifiable hard-override contribution deterministically, with a test for a finding that still survives on other axes.\n- [ ] The E2/F1/E6 rubrics and one new coaching move carry the ADR-0043 vocabulary; coaching remains non-prescriptive (states the evidence expectation, not the implementation).\n- [ ] Code-review gate behavior is byte-unchanged for findings without the new binaries (shared-kernel back-compat test).\n- [ ] make lint passes on the change.\n- [ ] make typecheck passes on the change.\n- [ ] make test passes on the change."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783890807020014001,"uuid":"dac0e39c-4cc0-49b1-9579-accf81325876"}